translated: Lindstrand, Filip Erland, high school teacher, Skövde, b. 22/4/94 in Götlunda, Skaraborg county. Son of L. A. Lindstrand and his wife H. H., born Lööf. Married on 21, m. Carin Wahlström. Children: Gudrun b. 22, married to Lieutenant Nils Berggren. Completed high school in Skövde in 13, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Uppsala in 20, worked as a substitute teacher at Gothenburg's high school for natural sciences from 21 to 22. Became a teacher in Östersund from 20 to 21, in Falköping from 22 to 36, and a mathematics and chemistry adjunct at Skövde's high school from 36, since 42 worked as secretary at the rector's office, acting principal in 39 and 40.
